Commands

Set up

git version
git config --list
git config user.name
git config user.email 
cat /home/anno/.gitconfig
git config --global color.ui true 

Basic stuff 

git clone URL
git log 
git init // Two ways to get a git repository. 
git add . // Adds whole directory. 
git status 
git commit 
git show // Shows the last commit. 
git apply 
git commit -a // Everything that has been tracked and modified and staged for commit. 
git add NAME // stages files for commit. 
git diff 
// You can unstage files.
 export EDITOR // Change editor from Nano to something else. 
git config --global core.editor emacs

Branching

Branching and merging. 
git branch NAME // Creates a new branch called NAME. 
git checkout NAME // Switches to NAME. New commits to NAME. 
gitk // Visualisation.
git merge NAME // Merges NAME to master. 
git branch --merged // shows all merged branch. 
git branch -d NAME // removes NAME from the merged branch. 
git branch ticketNUMBER // Creates a branch from an arbitrary change. 

Collaborate 

Uploads

git push add origin URL // git remote add origin https://github.com/verdastelo/Practicising_Git_2.git
git push origin // git push -u origin master 

Clone a file
Do the changes. 
git push origin master // Does the heavylifting. 
git fetch origin // To see contributions from others in your local server. 
git branch -a 

git blame gitNotes
git blame -C gitNotes


